import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data['actual'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of actual temperature recorded?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    data['normal'] = pd.to_datetime(data['normal'], errors='ignore')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='normal', data=data, label='Normal Temperature')
    
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

chart = plot(data)
